  "text": "The CL was enucleated from the ovary and dissected free of connective tissue as previously described [CITATION_1] . Subsequently, the CL was fixed with 10% formaldehyde and embedded in paraffin wax according to the standard histological technique. In addition, the remaining CL was prepared for molecular biological purposes. The CL tissue samples were collected, minced, immediately placed into a 1.5 mL microcentrifuge tube with or without 0.4 mL of TRIzol reagent (Invitrogen, Karlsruhe, Germany), and stored at 280uC until analysis.",
